### System Description and Purpose

**System Description:**
MyClinic OpenMRS is a cloud-hosted open-source electronic health record platform deployed on Amazon Web Services. The system provides the core clinical information management functions for MyClinic: patient registration and demographic management, clinical encounter documentation, medication management, laboratory result tracking, care plan management, and clinical reporting. OpenMRS is MyClinic's sole electronic health record system and the authoritative source of truth for all patient health information.

**Mission and Business Purpose:**
As documented in Task P-8 on Day 31, OpenMRS exists to support the safe, continuous, and coordinated delivery of patient care at MyClinic by providing a secure, reliable, and accurate system of record for all patient health information. The system enables clinicians to make informed care decisions, supports administrative operations and regulatory compliance, and protects the privacy of patients who have entrusted their most sensitive personal information to MyClinic's care.

**System Type:** Major Application — the system handles sensitive PHI and is critical to the primary mission of the organization

