### Technical Profile

**Hosting Environment:**
Amazon Web Services — Primary region specified based on MyClinic's operational location (e.g., us-east-1 for Eastern US deployments)

**AWS Account:**
MyClinic Production AWS Account — account number documented separately in the System Security Plan. Account should be enrolled in AWS Organizations under the MyClinic organizational unit with appropriate Service Control Policies applied.

**Primary Components:**
- EC2 instance (Ubuntu Linux) — OpenMRS application server; t3.medium or equivalent based on patient volume
- RDS MySQL — patient database; db.t3.medium or equivalent; Multi-AZ enabled
- S3 bucket — encrypted backup storage with Object Lock and versioning enabled
- VPC with public and private subnets — network isolation architecture
- AWS Certificate Manager — TLS certificate for HTTPS
- CloudWatch Logs — centralized log collection
- AWS CloudTrail — API activity audit logging
- Amazon GuardDuty — threat detection
- AWS Config — configuration compliance monitoring
- AWS Security Hub — centralized security findings aggregation

**Network Architecture:**
Application server in public subnet (HTTPS inbound only). Database in private subnet (no internet routing; accepts connections from application server security group only). VPC Flow Logs enabled. All components within MyClinic VPC — VPC ID documented in System Security Plan.

**External Connections:**
- Laboratory Information System — REST API integration; governed by BAA and Interconnection Security Agreement
- Email notification service — SMTP relay for system notifications; BAA required if notification content includes ePHI
- OpenMRS community distribution servers — software update source; integrity verified via checksum

