### Data Profile

**Data Types Handled:**
- Patient identity and demographic information (PHI)
- Clinical health records — diagnoses, medications, encounter notes, care plans (PHI — highest sensitivity)
- Laboratory and diagnostic results (PHI)
- User account and access control information
- Application audit logs
- Billing and financial information (PHI when combined with diagnosis codes)
- System configuration data

**Data Sensitivity:**
Protected Health Information (ePHI) under HIPAA. Highest organizational data sensitivity classification.

**Data Volume:**
Estimated patient population served by MyClinic — to be specified based on actual clinic size.

**Data Retention:**
Per applicable state medical records retention law (typically 6 years from date of service; longer for pediatric records). Documented retention and disposal policy maintained in System Security Plan.

**Re-identification Risk:**
De-identified analytics data derived from OpenMRS may carry re-identification risk for rare diagnoses or small population subgroups. Analytics data handling subject to case-by-case sensitivity review.

