### Change Management

**Change Notification Requirement:** The System Owner must notify the ISSO of any planned changes to the OpenMRS system — new integrations, infrastructure changes, software version changes, or significant configuration changes — before implementation. The ISSO assesses the security impact of proposed changes and updates the registration record and System Security Plan accordingly.

**Significant changes requiring registration update:**
- Addition of new external system integration
- Change in data types handled by the system
- Change in hosting environment or AWS region
- Change in system ownership or ISSO assignment
- Significant change in user population or access model
- Any change affecting the authorization boundary

