## Closing Out the Prepare Phase — A Look Back

Day 42 completes the Prepare step of the NIST RMF. Looking back at what has been built over the past three weeks:

**Organizational foundation (Days 21-24):** Full RMF overview, organizational roles and accountability structure, risk appetite and management strategy, enterprise risk assessment.

**System-level preparation (Days 25-35):** Risk register, control tailoring, common control identification, AWS security services, system impact categorization, stakeholder mapping, asset inventory, system boundary definition, information type classification.

**Deep documentation (Days 36-42):** Information lifecycle governance, threat and vulnerability analysis, risk analysis and register, security and privacy requirements, enterprise architecture alignment, requirements allocation, system registration.

The Prepare step was not setup. It was the foundation. Every piece of the categorization, control selection, assessment, and authorization work that comes next builds on what was established here.

